Unfortunately, the way the static methods are typed fails to successfully derive the passed emitter's event map when the object is constructed by a child class of EventEmitter, rather than EventEmitter itself.

```ts
import { EventEmitter, on, once } from 'node:events';

interface EventMap {
  'no-parameters': [];
  'with-parameters': [n: number, s: string];
}

const baseEmitter = new EventEmitter<EventMap>();
on(baseEmitter, 'no-parameters'); // AsyncIterableIterator<[]>
on(baseEmitter, 'with-parameters'); // AsyncIterableIterator<[n: number, s: string]>
once(baseEmitter, 'no-parameters'); // Promise<[]>
once(baseEmitter, 'with-parameters'); // Promise<[n: number, s: string]>

class DerivedEmitter extends EventEmitter<EventMap> {}

const derivedEmitter = new DerivedEmitter();
on(derivedEmitter, 'no-parameters'); // AsyncIterableIterator<any>
on(derivedEmitter, 'with-parameters'); // AsyncIterableIterator<any>
once(derivedEmitter, 'no-parameters'); // Promise<any>
once(derivedEmitter, 'with-parameters'); // Promise<any>

// Same occurs if DerivedEmitter is itself generic, eg.
class DerivedEmitter<Events extends Record<keyof Events, unknown[]>> extends EventEmitter<Events> {}
const derivedEmitter = new DerivedEmitter<EventMap>();
// ...etc.
```

With the derived emitters, the inferred EventMap type is of the form `{ [keyof EventMap]: any }`, keeping the keys but transmuting the tuples to `any`. I guess that since `Events` doesn't appear as a simple type anywhere in the interface signature, TS isn't able to correctly infer it. No idea what the best solution is.

Well that's very unfortunate.
This ultimately seems to be a limitation in the type system currently.
Take a look at this simplified example.
```ts
class Base<Generic> {}
class Derived extends Base<any> {}
type Infer<Type> = Type extends Base<infer Generic> ? Generic : never;
type Test = Infer<Derived>; // unknown
```

The resulting type is *always* unknown (or whatever `Generic` in the base is constrained to.) It appears we're lucky to even get inferred event names. I'd suggest to just pass the generics in this case unless someone has some genius idea for how to overcome this.
